ajor disciplines-Greek philosophy, biblical studies, and archaeology-produced lectures and papers on urbanism in the ancient world that reflect multihued perspectives that draw on the specialties of each contributor.Few conferences on urbanism engage in an interdisciplinary approach, and few deal with the questions raised in this book; even fewer are published and see the light of day. In this volume, we are pleased to be able to share a fine collection of essays from the conference with the larger community of people interested in the ancient world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh1 aArav, Rami, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArav, Rami, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBahat, Dan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrams, Laura W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreene, John T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreenspoon, Leonard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoddy, Nicolae, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Paul Allen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781575065878zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781575065878423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781575065878.jpg  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aG